name: Stars and Galaxies
description: This course surveys current ideas about the structure and evolution of astronomical objects ranging from the stars to the universe as a whole. This course is intended for "non-science" students as defined by the exclusion below. This course does not require AST101H5, but it may be combined with AST101H5 for a full-course credit in science for distribution purposes. [36L]
exclusions: AST121H1, AST201H1, AST210H1, AST221H1, AST222H1; ASTA02H3, ASTB23H3 and any 100 or higher level course in Chemistry or Physics with the exception of CHM110H5, CHM101H1, CHM135H1; PHY100H5, PHY100H1, PHY101H1, PHY201H1, PHY202H1, PHY205H.
